pom.xml stands for Project Object Model.
It's the configuration file used by Maven, a build automation tool for Java projects.

dependencies
Used to define external libraries (JARs) required by your project.
Maven will automatically download these from the Maven Central Repository.y and include them in your build path.

plugins
Define how to compile, run, and build the project
They perform specific tasks during the build process, such as:
✅ Compiling code
✅ Running tests
✅ Packaging the project into a JAR/ZIP
✅ Generating reports